  <title>GLib.slice_free_chain_with_offset</title>
  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
function slice_free_chain_with_offset(block_size: gsize, mem_chain: gpointer, next_offset: gsize): void {
    // Gjs wrapper for g_slice_free_chain_with_offset()
}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>Frees a linked list of memory blocks of structure type @type.</p>  <p>The memory blocks must be equal-sized, allocated via
<link xref="GLib.slice_alloc"/> or <link xref="GLib.slice_alloc0"/> and linked together by a
@next pointer (similar to <link xref="GLib.SList"/>). The offset of the @next
field in each block is passed as third argument.
Note that the exact release behaviour can be changed with the
[`G_DEBUG=gc-friendly`][G_DEBUG] environment variable, also see
[`G_SLICE`][G_SLICE] for related debugging options.</p>
  <p>Since 2.10</p>
